    <h1 class="mb-4">Google AI Overviews Click-Through Impact</h1>
    <p class="text-sm text-text-muted mb-8">Last updated: April 2026 | Rank4AI research</p>
    <div class="bg-off-white border-l-3 border-l-teal rounded-lg p-6 mb-8">
      <p class="text-[15px] text-teal font-medium leading-relaxed m-0"></p>
    </div>
CAPSLE: Google's AI Overviews are dramatically reducing organic click-through rates by 17% and paid clicks by 68%, fundamentally changing how users interact with search results.

<h2 class="mt-12 mb-4">The AI Overview Revolution</h2>

<p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">Google's AI Overviews have transformed the search landscape since their rollout. These AI-generated responses appear at the top of search results, providing instant answers to user queries. The impact has been swift and significant across all types of search traffic.</p>

<p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">Our analysis of 1,400+ SEO audits at Rank4AI reveals stark changes in user behaviour. Traditional search patterns are shifting as users increasingly rely on AI-generated summaries rather than clicking through to websites.</p>

<h2 class="mt-12 mb-4">Organic Traffic Takes a Major Hit</h2>

<p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">Organic click-through rates have dropped by 17% since AI Overviews became widespread. This decline affects websites across all industries and niches. The reduction is particularly pronounced for informational queries where AI Overviews provide comprehensive answers.</p>

<p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">Long-tail keywords that previously drove steady traffic are seeing significant drops. Users who would normally click through to read full articles now find their answers directly in the search results. This shift represents a fundamental change in how search traffic flows to websites.</p>

<p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">The 17% decline varies by query type. How-to searches and definition queries show the steepest drops. Product comparison searches maintain slightly higher click-through rates, though these are still declining steadily.</p>

<h2 class="mt-12 mb-4">Paid Clicks Collapse by 68%</h2>

<p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">The impact on paid search is even more dramatic. Google Ads click-through rates have plummeted by 68% for queries that trigger AI Overviews. This represents a catastrophic shift for businesses relying on paid search traffic.</p>

<p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">The positioning of AI Overviews above paid ads pushes traditional advertisements further down the page. Users satisfy their information needs before scrolling to see paid results. This placement hierarchy significantly reduces ad visibility and engagement.</p>

<p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">Cost-per-click rates are simultaneously increasing as advertisers compete for fewer available clicks. The combination of higher costs and lower volumes is squeezing advertising ROI across multiple sectors.</p>

<h2 class="mt-12 mb-4">How AI Overviews Cannibalise Traditional Results</h2>

<p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">AI Overviews function as comprehensive answer engines rather than simple search portals. They synthesise information from multiple sources and present it in digestible formats. This approach satisfies user intent without requiring clicks to external websites.</p>

<p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">The visual prominence of AI Overviews captures immediate attention. They occupy significant screen real estate, particularly on mobile devices. Traditional organic results appear smaller and less prominent by comparison.</p>

<p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">User behaviour patterns show increased time spent reading AI-generated content within search results. Scroll depth to traditional results has decreased substantially. Many users complete their search journey without ever clicking through to websites.</p>

<h2 class="mt-12 mb-4">Industry Impact Across Sectors</h2>

<p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">Publishing websites face the steepest traffic declines. News sites, blogs, and content platforms that rely on informational queries are particularly vulnerable. Recipe sites, how-to guides, and educational content providers report significant visitor reductions.</p>

<p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">E-commerce platforms experience mixed results. Product information queries show reduced click-through rates. However, commercial intent searches maintain better performance than purely informational queries.</p>

<p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">Local businesses see varied impacts depending on query types. Service-based searches often still require website visits for booking or contact information. Product-based local queries may be satisfied by AI Overview information alone.</p>

<h2 class="mt-12 mb-4">Adapting Your SEO Strategy</h2>

<p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">Understanding your specific AI Overview impact requires detailed analysis of search performance data. Traffic patterns, keyword rankings, and user engagement metrics all need evaluation in this new landscape.</p>

